1.Variables
-----------
In Programming,we use a variable to store data temporarily in a computer memory.
Ex:     let name = 'Mark';
        console.log(name);
        
  Naming rules:
  >Variable name cannot be a reserved keyword.
  >should be meaningful.
  >cannot start with a number.
  >cannot contain a space or hyphen(-).
  >Are Case-sensitive.
  
 
2.Constants
-------------
The value of a constant cannot change.
Ex:     const interestRate = 0.3;
        interestRate = 1;                   ///// Error
        console.log(interestRate);
        
 The difference between let and const variable is,In let we can reassign values but in const we cannot reassign value.
 
 3.Primitive Types
 ------------------
 Basically in JavaScript we have 2 categories of data types.
 (i)Primitives/Value Types        (ii) Reference Types
      String                          Object
      Number                          Array
      Boolean                         Function      
      Undefined
      null
 Ex:
      let name = 'Mark';
      let age = 30;
      let isApproved = true;
      let firstName;
      let selectedColors = null;
      
  4.Dynamic Typing
  ------------------
  The type of a variable can change at run time.
  
  Ex:   let name = 'Mark';
        console.log(name);
        
        name = 1;
        console.log(name);
        
  5.Objects
  -------------------
  An object in JavaScript is like an object in real life.
  Ex: A person.Every person has a name,age,address etc...
  
  When we are dealing with multiple related variables,we can put these variables inside of an object.
  
  Ex:          let person = {
                   name:'Mash',
                   age:30
                };
                
                //DOT notation
                person.name = 'John';
                console.log(person.name);
                
                //Bracket notation
                let selection = 'name';
                person[selection] = 'Mary';
                console.log(person);
                
 6.Arrays
 -------------
 An array is a data structure that we used to represent a list of items. 
 
        let selectedColors = ['red','blue']
        selectedColors[2] = 'green';
        console.log(selectedColors);
        
        selectedColors[2] = 1;
        console.log(selectedColors);
        console.log(selectedColors.length);
        
 7.Functions
 -----------------
 A Function is basically a set of statements that performs a task or calculate for a value.
 
 Ex:    function greet(name,lastName){
            console.log('Hello ' + name + ' ' + lastName);
        }
        
        greet('john','miller');
        
 8.Types of Function
 --------------------
 The above is for performing a task.There is also functions that calculates something.
        
 Ex:    function square(number){
          return number * number;
        }
        
        let number = square(2);
        console.log(number);
       
  
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
